                <note rend="inline" type="source">398.115 Tung or Wood Oil/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spiker</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-07-29T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 29, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 29—10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>177. My July 26, 9 p.m. Japanese Consul General states that Japanese authorities
                    concerned are now discussing possible means for shipment from Hankow of wood oil
                    belonging to the three interested American companies.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Chungking, Peiping, Shanghai. Shanghai repeat to Tokyo by
                    airmail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Spiker</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
